DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Serum Viscosity Outcome Upper Limit of Normal Integer::1 Decimal Place Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The 1 decimal place numeric laboratory value representing the upper level of the normal range of values of relative serum viscosity in a specimen.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to the result of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood for serum viscosity, the measure of the ability of the clear liquid part of the blood that remains after blood cells and clotting proteins have been removed to flow.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Property.preferredDefinition: The clear liquid part of the blood that remains after blood cells and clotting proteins have been removed.:The resistance of a liquid to sheer forces and flow.:Outcome; a phenomenon that follows and is caused by some previous phenomenon.

Concepts.definition: The clear portion of the blood that remains after the removal of the blood cells and the clotting proteins.
The resistance of a liquid to sheer forces and flow.
